<TITLE> Passports of DCC staffers seized </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 12 (bdnews24.com)  The special taskforce of the national coordination committee for curbing serious crimes Monday seized the passports of Dhaka City Corporation officers, employees and their family members. DCC public relations officer Abdur Rahman told bdnews24.com in the morning that the taskforce members seized the passports and took them away after sealing them in envelopes. DCC secretary Golam Mostafa ordered all corporation staffers to deposit their and family members' passports with the secretary's office within three days of receipt of the order, Rahman said. Anyone requiring their passport should apply stating the reason, he said quoting the order. Rahman said Sunday was the last day for depositing the passports. He could not say how many passports have been seized. Sources at the DCC said the corporation employs 4,940 first, second and third class permanent officers and employees. In addition, there are 7,272 more fourth class temporary employees in the master roll. bdnew
